    "descriptionModule": {
      "briefSummary": "Study hypothesis: Comparing the effect of digoxin and ivabradine in chronic heart failure patients with a left ventricular ejection of 35% or lower and sinus rhythm with heart rate 70 beats per minute or higher, and who are taking maximal dose of a beta blocker if tolerated.",
      "detailedDescription": "Selected patients have chronic heart failure with left ventricular systolic dysfunction and sinus rhythm. They take optimal medical therapy."
    },
